Class Applicant

java.lang.Object
entities.User
entities.Applicant
All Implemented Interfaces:
Filter
Direct Known Subclasses:
Officer
public class Applicant extends User
Represents an Applicant in the system. The Applicant can apply for projects, view available projects, manage their applications, and interact with enquiries.

      Constructs an Applicant with the provided details.

      nric - The NRIC of the applicant.
      age - The age of the applicant.
      maritalStatus - The marital status of the applicant.
      password - The password of the applicant.
      isVisible - Whether the applicant's details are visible in the system.
      ac - The AuthenticationController instance for the applicant's authentication.
      role - The role of the user (should be ROLE.APPLICANT).

      public void applyForProject(String projectName, String flatType)
      Allows the applicant to apply for a project with the specified project name and flat type. The application is saved to the project application database.
      Parameters:
      projectName - The name of the project to apply for.
      flatType - The type of flat the applicant is applying for.

    • viewProjects

      Parameters:
